window.EQ_DATA["GOOGL"] = {"ticker": "GOOGL", "meta": {"ticker": "GOOGL", "nome_empresa": "Alphabet Inc.", "setor": "Internet / Digital Advertising / AI", "geografia": "US", "moeda_reporte": "USD", "market_cap_usd_bn": "~2200", "fiscal_year_end": "31 de dezembro", "tags": ["setor/internet", "setor/digital-ads", "setor/cloud", "setor/ai-infra", "geografia/us", "moat/rede", "moat/dados", "status/em_estudo"], "status_tese": "em_estudo", "data_criacao": "2026-04-21", "ultima_atualizacao": "2026-06-03"}, "views": {"ov": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h1>GOOGL — Alphabet Inc.</h1>\n<blockquote><strong>One-liner</strong>: #1 global em digital advertising (Search + YouTube), #3 hyperscaler (GCP, atrás de AWS e <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MSFT\" title=\"wiki/MSFT\">Azure</a>), dono do TPU (maior ASIC AI custom do mundo). Em simultâneo: (1) defendendo Search contra AI disruption, (2) monetizando YouTube, (3) expandindo GCP, (4) Other Bets (Waymo, DeepMind). <strong>🆕 Q1 FY26 (filed 2026-04-29): Cloud +63% YoY, backlog quase dobrou QoQ pra $460B (&gt;AWS pela 1ª vez), Cloud margin 32.9% (de 23.7% FY25), 350M paid subs, Waymo &gt;500K rides/week, Gemini API 16B tokens/min (+60% QoQ). Search +19% (queries all-time high). EPS $5.11 inclui $2.35 de equity gains não-recorrentes — operating EPS ~$2.76.</strong> <strong>🆕🆕 03-Jun-2026: Alphabet anuncia equity offering hoje + revisa CapEx FY26 UP de $175-185B → $180-190B + sinaliza &quot;significant increase&quot; em FY27. Tokens 3.2Q/mês (330x vs 2024), 900M Gemini App MAU (2.25x YoY), serving cost Gemini -78% em 2025, AI Overviews 2.5B+ MAU, AI Mode 1B+ MAU. Pro-forma debt $102B inclui ~$20B May 2026 bond issuance em 3 currencies.</strong></blockquote></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>O negócio</h2><h3>Search (cash cow e maior business)</h3>\n<p>~57% da receita. <strong>Moat único</strong>: 20+ anos de search query data, algoritmos refinados, queries/day &gt;8B, revenue $198B FY24.</p>\n<p><strong>AI threat</strong>: ChatGPT+Perplexity+Claude capturaram parte das queries que antes iam pro Google. GOOGL respondeu com &quot;AI Overviews&quot; e &quot;AI Mode&quot; — integrando Gemini direto nos resultados. Dado ainda misto.</p>\n<h3>YouTube (under-monetized giant)</h3>\n<p>Dominância em long-form video + crescimento agressivo em Shorts. YouTube: <strong>2.74B viewers globais</strong>, ARPU $1.37 (vs Netflix $4.31 ARPV). YouTube Ads $36B FY24 + YouTube Premium (não disclosed separately).</p>\n<h3>Google Cloud (GCP) — acelerando</h3>\n<p>$43B FY24 (+31% YoY). Historicamente #3 hyperscaler atrás de AWS/Azure. Vantagem: TPU ecosystem, BigQuery. Operating margin melhorando mas ainda atrás de Azure/AWS.</p>\n<h3>Other Bets</h3>\n<p>Waymo (robotaxi), Verily (healthcare), X (moonshots). Revenue $1.6B (tiny), losses persistentes. <strong>Waymo</strong> é a optionality principal — escalando commercial fleet.</p>\n<h3>TPU — ativo único</h3>\n<p>Google desenha TPU em parceria com <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">Broadcom</a>. TPU v7p Ironwood (N3, HBM3e 192GB) em ramp 2025-26. <strong>2.7-3M units de TPU em 2026</strong> (vs 1.5M em 2025). Expõe TPU pra Anthropic (1M units deal). Maior comprador de ASIC customizado do mundo. Ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Management</h2><ul><li><strong>CEO</strong>: Sundar Pichai (desde 2015 Google CEO, 2019 Alphabet CEO)</li><li><strong>CFO</strong>: Ruth Porat → Anat Ashkenazi (desde Jul/2024)</li><li><strong>Founders</strong>: Larry Page + Sergey Brin — saíram do dia-a-dia 2019, retornaram parcialmente 2023 pra supervisionar AI. Detêm classe B voting control.</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Structure</strong>: Alphabet holding, Google é subsidiária principal + Other Bets separadas.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Financeiros</h2><p>Os dados do recap Paulo (2024-recap.md) já estão na tabela acima. <strong>[ ] Números FY25 específicos a verificar</strong> — 10-K FY25 (filed Feb/2026) não está no vault.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Update Apr/2026 — Kurian / FT [[raw-md/GOOGL/2026-04-FT-Kurian-Google-Cloud-AI-edge]]</h2><p>Stephen Morris (FT) entrevistou Thomas Kurian (CEO Google Cloud, há 8 anos no cargo, ex-Oracle) em Las Vegas durante evento de revelação dos novos TPUs (8ª geração).</p>\n<h3>Highlights estratégicos</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Google Cloud market share cresceu de 7% para 14%</strong> sob Kurian (8 anos)</li><li><strong>Cloud market total: $418bn</strong></li><li>Permanece <strong>distant third</strong> atrás de AWS e Azure, mas <strong>closing gap via AI</strong></li><li><strong>FY26E GCP: &gt;$70bn</strong> (vs $43bn FY24 = ~+63% em 2 anos via FY26E)</li></ul>\n<h3>Tese &quot;full-stack&quot; diferenciada</h3>\n<blockquote>&quot;We&#x27;re not just a hyperscaler reselling other people&#x27;s technology. Our differentiation comes down to the fact that we own the IP, the model and the chips are ours. <strong>For every dollar of revenue, we&#x27;re not shipping 80 per cent of it to either a model or chip provider, which allows us to invest more.</strong>&quot;</blockquote>\n<p>Implicação: vs MSFT (depende da OpenAI) e AMZN (depende em grande parte da Anthropic + NVDA), Google é <strong>vertically integrated</strong> — DeepMind + Gemini + TPU + GCP infra + Search. Permite <strong>capex mais eficiente em ROIC</strong>.</p>\n<h3>TPUs — 8ª geração revelada Apr/2026</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>2 novos TPUs</strong>: 1 para training, 1 com mais memória para inference</li><li>Sucessor do <strong>Ironwood (v7p)</strong> que ainda está em ramp 2025-26</li><li>Co-designed com <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">Broadcom</a></li></ul>\n<h3>Market share AI compute (Epoch AI report)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Google: ~25% global AI compute</strong> = <strong>3,8mn TPUs + 1,3mn GPUs NVDA</strong></li><li><strong>Microsoft #2: 3,2mn NVDA GPUs</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>Anthropic deal (24-Apr-2026, sexta-feira anterior ao artigo)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Google investe até $40bn no Anthropic</strong></li><li><strong>Provê 5GW de computing capacity ao longo de 5 anos = &gt;$200bn</strong></li><li>Anthropic vai comprar <strong>mais TPUs</strong> (ampliando o deal de 1mn TPU prévio)</li></ul>\n<h3>Tensão NVDA-Google (relevante para <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a>)</h3>\n<ul><li>Jensen Huang em podcast: criticou Google por não submeter chips a benchmarks independentes; afirmou que <strong>&quot;100% da demanda TPU veio do Anthropic&quot;</strong></li><li>Resposta de Kurian: <strong>9 dos top 10 AI labs usam TPUs</strong> (incluindo Thinking Machines da Mira Murati). OpenAI <strong>não pode</strong> usar TPU por exclusivity deal MSFT.</li></ul>\n<h3>CapEx</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>CapEx 2026 forecast: $185bn</strong> (artigo) — bem acima da estimativa anterior do recap Paulo (~$75B FY25E)</li><li><strong>Driver</strong>: customer demand + strong revenue growth justificando</li></ul>\n<h3>Outlook setor (Kurian view)</h3>\n<ul><li>OpenAI + Anthropic levantaram <strong>&gt;$150bn em 2026</strong> (private fundraising)</li><li>Lossmaking sustentado é problema: &quot;cannot raise venture money forever&quot;</li><li><strong>Shakeout esperado em 1-2 anos</strong> entre AI providers — quem não tiver economics não sobrevive</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Update Set/2025 — Kurian @ GS Communacopia [[raw-md/GOOGL/2025-09-GS-Communacopia-Kurian]]</h2><p>Conferência Goldman Sachs, set/2025, Eric Sheridan entrevistando Kurian. <strong>Insights novos sobre tech competitiveness</strong>:</p>\n<h3>Hardware moat — TPUs específicos</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>11 anos</strong> já construindo AI systems e chips</li><li><strong>2x power efficiency</strong> (2x flops per watt) vs próximo concorrente</li><li><strong>50% performance delta</strong> vs outros players</li><li><strong>Capacity total</strong>: maior que o próximo player no segmento</li><li><strong>Storage AI-specific</strong>: low latency para inference, scale-out cluster eficientemente</li></ul>\n<h3>Demand de 4 customer segments</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>AI Labs</strong>: <strong>9 das 10 maiores AI labs</strong> são customers (consistente com FT article 2026-04)</li><li><strong>Traditional enterprises</strong> deployando AI models</li><li><strong>Capital markets</strong>: shift de classical computation → inference para high-frequency calculations</li><li><strong>High-performance computing</strong>: SSI (Safe Superintelligence Inc), LG Electronics, LG AI</li></ol>\n<h3>Modelos — 4 categorias da Alphabet</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Gemini</strong> (large-scale generative AI) — usado por <strong>9M developers</strong>; Gemini 2.5 alcançou 1tn tokens <strong>20x mais rápido</strong> que 1.5</li><li><strong>Diffusion models</strong> (Imagen, Veo, Lyria, Chirp) — image/video/audio/speech</li><li><strong>Scientific computation models</strong> — recém adicionado</li><li><strong>Plus 182 leading models</strong> de outros providers integrados</li></ul>\n<h3>Why Google Cloud está ganhando (Kurian)</h3>\n<ul><li>Deep product differentiation em performance/cost/reliability/efficiency em AI infra</li><li>Best-in-class generative AI models</li><li>Domain-specific AI applications + agents (anos de trabalho dando frutos)</li><li>Resultado: capturing new customers faster + deepening relationships + growing TAM</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Update Mar/2026 — Ashkenazi @ MS TMT [[raw-md/GOOGL/2026-03-MS-TMT-Ashkenazi]]</h2><p>Morgan Stanley TMT Conference, mar/2026, Brian Nowak entrevistando Ashkenazi (CFO). <strong>Insights sobre disciplina de capital</strong>:</p>\n<h3>CapEx analysis framework (Ashkenazi)</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Continuum approach</strong>: análise por horizonte temporal<ul><li>Near-term + certain (Search compute, Cloud compute) → high confidence ROI</li><li>Longer-term, earlier innovation (Waymo, frontier models) → lower confidence mas big upside</li></ul></li><li><strong>Foundational layer</strong>: Gemini + frontier models tornam os investments mais defensáveis ao longo do continuum</li></ul>\n<h3>CapEx driver disclosure</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>FY25 actuals: $91bn</strong> (vs guidance original $70-75bn — <strong>+22% over-shoot</strong>)<ul><li>Driver da revisão: aceleração de demand (sempre exited quarter com <strong>demand &gt; supply</strong> em Cloud)</li><li>Plus: aceleração de construção de data centers (oportunidade de pull-in)</li></ul></li><li><strong>FY26 guidance: ~$180bn</strong> (consistent com Q4 call $175-185bn)</li><li><strong>60% chips, 40% data centers + networking</strong> — proporção mantida</li></ul>\n<h3>&quot;Investor sentiment changed&quot;</h3>\n<ul><li>1 ano atrás: hallway/Wall Street talks eram sobre &quot;search disruption&quot; e &quot;long-term positioning vs ChatGPT&quot;</li><li>Agora ($4tn market cap): sentiment changed dramatically — execução AI virou narrative positivo</li><li>Implícito: mid-2025 foi o turning point (Q3+Q4 FY25 results)</li></ul>\n<h3>Demand &gt; Supply é tema recorrente</h3>\n<blockquote>&quot;We always have now said multiple quarters in a row that we exited the quarter with more demand for our Cloud services than we had supply.&quot;</blockquote>\n<p>Implicação: <strong>CapEx $180bn não é speculative — é resposta a demand já contratada</strong> ($240bn backlog Q4 FY25 = ~3,4 anos de revenue).</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Q1 FY26 — primeiro reality check pós-FY25 (29-Apr-2026)</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-07</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-press-release\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-press-release\">Alphabet Q1 2026 press release oficial</a> (period ended 2026-03-31, release date 2026-04-29).</p>\n<h3>Headline metrics Q1 FY26</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Total revenue</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$90.2B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$109.9B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+22%</strong> (+19% cc)</td></tr><tr><td>Operating income</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$30.6B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$39.7B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+30%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Operating margin</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">34%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>36.1%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+2pp</td></tr><tr><td>Net income (GAAP)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$34.5B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$62.6B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+81%</td></tr><tr><td>Diluted EPS (GAAP)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$2.81</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$5.11</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+82%</td></tr><tr><td>Diluted EPS ex-equity-gain</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$2.81</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>~$2.76</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-2% (incluindo +16% normalizado se ajusta Q1 25)</td></tr><tr><td>OCF Q1</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$36.2B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$45.8B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+27%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>CapEx Q1</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$17.2B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$35.7B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+107%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FCF Q1</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$19.0B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$10.1B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-47%</td></tr><tr><td>FCF TTM</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$64.4B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Por segmento</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 25 ($M)</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 26 ($M)</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">OI Q1 26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">OI margin</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Google Search &amp; other</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">50,702</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>60,399</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+19%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td></tr><tr><td>YouTube ads</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">8,927</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">9,883</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+11%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td></tr><tr><td>Google Network</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">7,256</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">6,971</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-4%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td></tr><tr><td>Subscriptions/platforms/devices</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">10,379</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">12,384</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+19%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Google Services total</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>77,264</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>89,637</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+16%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$40.6B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>45.3%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Google Cloud</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>12,260</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>20,028</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+63%</strong> ←</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$6.6B (+203%)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>32.9%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Other Bets</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">450</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">411</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-9%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$2.1B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/m</td></tr><tr><td>Alphabet-level (shared AI R&amp;D)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$5.4B (-78% YoY)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/m</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>90,234</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>109,896</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+22%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$39.7B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>36.1%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Cloud aceleração estrutural — trajetória trimestral</strong></h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Trimestre</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">GCP YoY</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">OI margin</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Q1 FY25</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+28%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">17.8%</td></tr><tr><td>Q2 FY25</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+32%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td></tr><tr><td>Q3 FY25</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+34%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td></tr><tr><td>Q4 FY25</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+48%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">30.1%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Q1 FY26</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+63%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>32.9%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>5 trimestres de aceleração contínua YoY</strong>. Margin expansion de <strong>17.8% → 32.9% = +15pp</strong> em 12 meses. Inflexão estrutural confirmada — não foi flash 1-trimestre.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Cloud backlog $460B — supera AWS pela 1ª vez</strong></h3>\n<p>Sundar quote literal: <em>&quot;Google Cloud revenues grew 63% with <strong>backlog nearly doubling quarter on quarter to over $460 billion</strong>&quot;</em>.</p>\n<p><strong>Trajetória do backlog GCP</strong> (recuperado dos earnings calls anteriores):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Período</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Backlog</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">QoQ</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Q3 FY25</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$155B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+46% (Q2 base)</td></tr><tr><td>Q4 FY25</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$240B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+55%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>&gt;2x</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Q1 FY26</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$460B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+92% (~2x)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>~3x</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Cross-comparison crítico vs AWS</strong> (ver <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">AWS Q1 FY26</th><th style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>GCP Q1 FY26</strong></th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Diferença</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Backlog</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$364B (WAL 5.5y)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$460B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>GCP &gt; AWS pela 1ª vez</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Run rate ($/ano)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$150B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$80B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">AWS ainda 1.9x maior</td></tr><tr><td>YoY growth</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+28%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+63%</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">GCP 2.25x mais rápido</td></tr><tr><td>Backlog/run rate</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">2.4x</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>5.75x</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">GCP tem <strong>2.4x mais visibility</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ <strong>Implicação</strong>: o gap AMZN→GOOGL no Cloud está fechando rápido. Em magnitude absoluta de revenue AWS ainda lidera; mas em <strong>demand contratada forward</strong> GCP virou o líder. Catalisa re-rating estrutural se trajetória confirmar nos próximos 2-3 trimestres.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Outros disclosures relevantes</strong></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>350M paid subscriptions</strong> (vs 300M no Q3 FY25, 270M Q1 FY25) — YouTube + Google One são drivers principais. Crescimento +30% em 12 meses.</li><li><strong>Gemini Enterprise paid MAU: +40% QoQ</strong> — momentum forte em monetização B2B.</li><li><strong>Gemini API: &gt;16B tokens/min via direct API</strong>, <strong>+60% QoQ</strong>. Acelerou meaningful em developer adoption.</li><li><strong>Waymo &gt;500,000 fully autonomous rides/week</strong> — primeiro disclosure desta magnitude. Em Q3 FY25 era ~250k/week (mencionado na call). <strong>2x em ~6 meses</strong>.</li><li><strong>Search queries em all-time high</strong> — AI experiences NÃO erodiram volume, ao contrário, &quot;driving usage&quot;. +19% revenue YoY.</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Other income &amp; equity gains — limpando o EPS</strong></h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;For Q1 2026, the net effect of the gain on equity securities of $36.9 billion increased the provision for income tax, net income, and diluted net income per share by $8.2 billion, $28.7 billion, and $2.35, respectively.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<ul><li><strong>Equity securities gain $36.9B</strong> → após tax $8.2B = $28.7B net income impact = <strong>$2.35/share</strong></li><li>EPS reportado <strong>$5.11</strong> — mas <strong>$2.35 é one-off de mark-to-market</strong> de equity stakes (Anthropic principalmente, e outros)</li><li><strong>Operating EPS Q1 26: $2.76</strong> ≈ -2% YoY vs $2.81 — mais saudável e comparable</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Stake de equity disclosure</strong>: Non-marketable securities saltaram de $68.7B (Dec 31, 25) para <strong>$106.9B (Mar 31, 26)</strong> = <strong>+$38.2B QoQ</strong>. Reflete principalmente o mark-up das equity stakes em AI labs (Anthropic, etc.). Paralelo direto ao que AMZN reportou ($16.8B Anthropic mark-up no mesmo trimestre — mas GOOGL é maior).</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Capital allocation — buyback ZERO + bond $31B + M&amp;A $33.6B</strong></h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Item</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Q1 FY26</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Buyback</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$15.1B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$0</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Dividend</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$2.4B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$2.5B (+5% rate)</td></tr><tr><td>Bond issuance (gross)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$4.5B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$31.4B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Acquisitions (cash)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$0.3B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$33.6B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Long-term debt (BS)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">n/a</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$46.5B → $77.5B (+$31B)</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Mesmo padrão da AMZN</strong>: capital allocation 100% para AI infra + M&amp;A, <strong>buyback congelado</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>M&amp;A $33.6B em Q1 26</strong> + Goodwill +$24B QoQ = consistente com <strong>closing da aquisição da Wiz</strong> ($32B deal anunciado em Mar/2024 — provavelmente fechou em Q1 FY26).</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 CapEx +107% YoY</strong></h3>\n<ul><li>Q1 FY26 CapEx: <strong>$35.7B</strong> (vs $17.2B Q1 FY25)</li><li>Run-rate annualized = ~$143B → ainda <strong>abaixo do guidance FY26 $175-185B</strong></li><li>Implica aceleração nos Q2-Q4 (tipicamente ramp ao longo do ano)</li><li>D&amp;A Q1: $6.5B (+44% YoY) — confirma Ashkenazi disclosure de &quot;D&amp;A growth rate em 2026 vai acelerar em Q1&quot;</li></ul>\n<h3>Implicações para tese (delta vs Q4 FY25)</h3>\n<p>✓ <strong>Cloud hipergrowth confirmado</strong>: aceleração trimestre-a-trimestre +28→+32→+34→+48→<strong>+63%</strong> = 5 quarters straight. Não é mean reversion. ✓ <strong>Backlog $460B = ~5.75 anos de revenue contratada</strong> (a run rate atual ~$80B/ano). Visibility extraordinária — maior que AWS em absoluto pela primeira vez. ✓ <strong>Cloud margin 32.9%</strong> equipara/supera AWS (AWS Q1 FY26 era 37.7% mas em base ~2x maior). GCP virou estruturalmente comparable. ✓ <strong>Search resiliente</strong>: +19% revenue, queries all-time high. Tese &quot;AI Mode staunching share losses&quot; do research <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=initiate-outperform-AI-mode\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/initiate-outperform-AI-mode\">initiate-outperform-AI-mode</a> validada. ✓ <strong>Subscription business 350M</strong> — proxy de monetization platforms maduro. ✓ <strong>Waymo 500K+ rides/week</strong> — escala que justifica Other Bets continuar consumindo capital. ⚠️ <strong>EPS $5.11 é distorted</strong>: $2.35 de equity gain não-recorrente. Operating EPS $2.76 é o número justo pra valuation comparativo. ⚠️ <strong>CapEx accelerando</strong>: $35.7B Q1 → run rate $143B → vai ter que escalar mais nos próximos Qs pra atingir $175-185B FY26 guide. <strong>D&amp;A growth também acelerando</strong> (Ashkenazi pre-anunciou). ⚠️ <strong>Other Bets loss -$2.1B (-71% pior YoY)</strong> + Alphabet-level shared R&amp;D -$5.4B (-78% pior YoY) — drag combinado de <strong>$7.5B/trimestre vs $4.3B Q1 25</strong>. Pressão crescente em GAAP consolidated mesmo com Cloud explodindo.</p>\n<h3>Cross-implications</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> — <strong>GCP backlog $460B &gt; AWS $364B</strong> = primeiro trimestre em que GCP lidera demand contratada. Reforça questionamento de &quot;AWS é hyperscaler #1&quot; pra investors. Cross-link em AMZN com este datapoint.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> — GCP $20B + CapEx $35.7B Q1 → demand sustentada de TPU custom (AVGO partnership). Ironwood ramp + 8ª geração revelada Apr/2026.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> — Jensen criticou Google em Apr/2026; mas Google é major NVDA customer (1.3M GPUs ativos). GCP +63% reforça <strong>multi-vendor accelerator strategy</strong> dos hyperscalers.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — Alphabet alone: $35.7B Q1 + $147B AWS TTM + Meta + MSFT = setor passa de $700B/ano CapEx anualizado. Sustained demand-pull.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> — GCP +63% growth com TPU stack próprio = mais um data point estrutural pro shift custom silicon. Alongside AMZN Trainium.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Q1 FY26 10-Q — disclosures novas vs press release (filed 2026-05-07)</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-05-07</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">10-Q SEC, 54 páginas, OCR&amp;#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime — PDF tinha text layer mas com font encoding scrambled, OCR forçado</a>. Foco: itens <strong>não cobertos</strong> no press release ingerido em 2026-05-07.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Backlog total $467.6B (vs $460B Cloud-only no press release)</strong></h3>\n<p>Press release deu apenas o número Cloud (~$460B). 10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-12\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-12\">p.12</a>) detalha:</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;As of March 31, 2026, we had <strong>$467.6 billion of remaining performance obligations (&#x27;revenue backlog&#x27;), of which $462.3 billion related to Google Cloud</strong>. Revenue backlog represents commitments in customer contracts that have not yet been recognized as revenue.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Bucket</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Backlog Q1 26</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Total Alphabet</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$467.6B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Google Cloud (specific)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$462.3B</td></tr><tr><td>Outros (Search/YouTube enterprise/etc.)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$5.3B</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>⚠️ Methodology change importante</strong>: <em>&quot;In the first quarter of 2026, we elected to change our reporting of revenue backlog to now also include contracts with an original expected term of one year or less.&quot;</em></p>\n<p>→ A comparação com Q4 25 ($240B) <strong>não é apples-to-apples</strong> — agora inclui contratos curtos. O salto QoQ &quot;+92%&quot; é uma combinação de (a) novos deals + (b) mudança metodológica. <strong>Não dá para isolar quanto é cada efeito</strong>, mas o press release transmitiu o número como se fosse apenas growth.</p>\n<p><strong>&quot;We expect to recognize just over 50% of the revenue backlog as...&quot;</strong> [revenue nos próximos ~24 meses inferido da WAL]</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Wiz acquisition — closed 11-Mar-2026 por $29.5B (vs $32B anunciado em 2024)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-26\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-26\">p.26</a>) detalha alocação do purchase price:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Componente</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Valor</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Goodwill (alocado a GCP)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$22.7B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Intangibles</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$8.3B</strong></td></tr><tr><td>— Patents and developed technology (7yr useful life)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$3.6B</td></tr><tr><td>— Customer relationships (10yr useful life)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$4.5B</td></tr><tr><td>— Trade names (7yr)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$0.2B</td></tr><tr><td>Net liabilities assumed</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$1.5B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total purchase price</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$29.5B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ Goodwill <strong>NÃO é dedutível para tax</strong>. Amortização de intangibles começa em Q2 26 → headwind menor de margem cloud nos próximos quarters.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Intersect acquisition — DC capacity acceleration play (NOVO)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-26\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-26\">p.26</a>) — <strong>acquisition COMPLETED 10-Mar-2026 por $5.9B</strong> — não anunciada no press release:</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;This acquisition enables acceleration of data center capacity and energy [transition]&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Componente</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Valor</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Property and equipment</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$5.1B</td></tr><tr><td>Goodwill (alocado GS + GCP)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$2.2B</td></tr><tr><td>Debt assumed</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$1.2B</td></tr><tr><td>Net liabilities assumed</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$0.2B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total purchase price</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$5.9B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Implicação</strong>: Intersect é developer de <strong>renewable energy</strong> — aquisição <strong>vertical</strong> de capacity de DC + energia. Confirma o framing Ashkenazi de &quot;demand &gt; supply&quot; — GOOGL está <strong>comprando capacity</strong> para acelerar deployment, não só construindo orgânico.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 GFiber pending divestiture (NOVO)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-26\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-26\">p.26</a>) — assinado em Mar/2026, fechamento esperado late 2026:</p>\n<ul><li>Recebem $1.5B cash + $2.0B note receivable + 49.99% equity interest</li><li>$6.8B de PP&amp;E reclassificada como held-for-sale</li><li>GFiber sai dos resultados consolidados após close</li><li>Pequeno cleanup de Other Bets — não material no contexto, mas sinaliza foco Sundar em concentrar capital nos drivers principais</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Waymo recebeu $16.0B funding em Fev/2026 — &quot;significant majority&quot; do Alphabet</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-40\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-40\">p.40</a>) — <strong>disclosure novo</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;In February 2026, Waymo received $16.0 billion in funding, the significant majority of which was funded by Alphabet.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ Waymo está consumindo <strong>~$16B de capital interno</strong> = magnitude que vai pesar ainda mais nas linhas Other Bets / Alphabet-level activities. Loss Other Bets Q1 26 = <strong>-$2.1B (vs -$1.2B Q1 25, +71% pior)</strong> já reflete parte desse ramp.</p>\n<p>→ <strong>Combina com o disclosure das 500K rides/week</strong> (Sundar Pichai press release): Waymo está em ramp acelerado, mas custo está <strong>explícito agora</strong> (era opacidade antes).</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 OpenAI/Anthropic-style equity commitment $40B explicitado (NOVO no 10-Q vs press release)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-22\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-22\">p.22</a>) — futuro funding commitments saltaram de $1.1B (Dec 25) para <strong>$40.7B (Mar 26)</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;As of March 31, 2026, this amount includes commitments for a future private investment consisting of a <strong>$10.0 billion capital commitment and $30.0 billion of future capital funding</strong> accounted for as an equity derivative.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>E na MD&amp;A (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-40\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-40\">p.40</a>):</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;In March 2026, we committed to a <strong>$40.0 billion investment in a private company</strong> consisting of a $10.0 billion [direct investment] and $30.0 billion of future capital funding contingent upon the achievement of specified operational and financial milestones [through 2030].&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ Este é o <strong>deal Anthropic já reportado em Apr/2026</strong> ($40B + 5GW), agora <strong>formalizado em 10-Q</strong> com mecânica:</p>\n<ul><li>$10B direct equity (no balance sheet via non-marketable securities)</li><li>$30B equity derivative — futuro funding contingent em milestones operacionais/financeiros até 2030</li><li>Notional do equity derivative aparece em derivatives table = $30B (vs $0 em Dec 31, 25)</li></ul>\n<p>→ <strong>Cross-link com AMZN</strong>: AMZN tem facility de $20B + $5B option + $5B prefs forward em Anthropic = ~$30B forward. <strong>GOOGL tem $40B forward em Anthropic (presumível)</strong> = <strong>maior do que AMZN no próprio Anthropic</strong>, embora AMZN tenha mais acumulado já desembolsado ($74B).</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 TPU sendo VENDIDO externamente — novo business model (NOVO)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-38\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-38\">p.38</a>):</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We have signed a limited number of agreements to supply Tensor Processing Units (TPU) hardware to customers who [require or provide on-premises infrastructure for specialized, high-scale workloads]&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ <strong>Mudança estrutural</strong>: GOOGL tradicionalmente alugava TPU via GCP (consumption-based). Agora <strong>vende hardware</strong> para customers que precisam on-prem. Paralelo ao &quot;AMZN sell Trainium racks externally — good chance over next couple of years&quot; (Andy Jassy Q1 FY26 call). Ambos os hyperscalers começando <strong>monetização standalone do custom silicon</strong>.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Long-term debt issuance Q1 26 = $30.4B em 3 currencies</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-22\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-22\">p.22</a>) — breakdown completo:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Tranche</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Tamanho</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Coupon avg</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">WAL</th><th>Maturidades</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>2026 USD Notes</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$20.0B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">4.80%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">15 anos</td><td>2029-2066</td></tr><tr><td><strong>2026 Sterling Notes</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>£5.5B (~$7.3B)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">5.31%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>31 anos</strong></td><td>2029-2126</td></tr><tr><td><strong>2026 Swiss Franc Notes</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>CHF 3.1B (~$3.8B)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">1.06%</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">10 anos</td><td>2029-2051</td></tr><tr><td><strong>TOTAL</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>~$31.1B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-</td><td>-</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<ul><li>Sterling tranche tem <strong>WAL de 31 anos</strong> (até 2126!) — locking in cost of capital ultra-longo prazo</li><li>Total LT debt: $46.5B → <strong>$77.5B (+$31B QoQ)</strong></li><li>Total fair value Notes: $45.6B → <strong>$75.3B</strong></li><li>Combina com <strong>$3.5T market cap</strong> = leverage ainda baixíssima (LT debt/MC ~2.2%), mas ritmo de issuance acelerou</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Cross-comparison capital allocation hyperscalers Q1 26:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>AMZN: bond issuance <strong>$53.8B</strong> (USD $37B + EUR €14.5B), LT debt $66B → $119B</li><li>GOOGL: bond issuance <strong>$31.1B</strong> (USD $20B + GBP £5.5B + CHF 3.1B), LT debt $47B → $78B</li><li>Soma: <strong>&gt;$85B</strong> em bond issuance em UM trimestre por dois players, todos pra fundar AI infra</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Credit derivatives = financial guarantees a third-party DCs ($43.7B post-quarter)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-18\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-18\">p.18</a>) — disclosures sobre backstops:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Período</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Notional credit derivatives</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dec 31, 2025</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$16.9B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mar 31, 2026</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$28.4B</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>+ April 2026 (post-quarter)</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+$15.3B</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>TOTAL post-quarter</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>~$43.7B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;In April, 2026, we entered into additional agreements with certain third parties to backstop certain obligations relating to third-party data centers...&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ GOOGL está <strong>financeiramente garantindo capacity de DC de terceiros</strong> — modelo similar ao Meta (third-party cloud arrangements bridge para 2026-27 mencionado no Q1 follow-up). A escala ($43.7B) sugere que GCP está fazendo bridge de capacity via parceiros enquanto constrói próprios DCs (lease commitments $75.6B + Intersect M&amp;A).</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 PP&amp;E &quot;assets not yet in service&quot; +$30B QoQ (NOVO detalhe)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-24\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-24\">p.24</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Categoria PP&amp;E</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Dec 31, 2025</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Mar 31, 2026</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Δ</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Technical infrastructure</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$203.7B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$217.9B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+$14.2B</td></tr><tr><td>Office space</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$48.3B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$48.8B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+$0.4B</td></tr><tr><td>Corporate and other</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$14.5B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$5.9B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$8.5B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>In service</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$266.5B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$272.6B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+$6.1B</td></tr><tr><td>Less: accumulated depreciation</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$98.5B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$100.2B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-$1.7B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Add: assets NOT yet in service</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$78.6B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$108.6B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+$30.0B</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>PP&amp;E net</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$246.6B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$281.0B</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+$34.4B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ <strong>Assets not yet in service = $108.6B</strong> = capacidade já comprada/construída mas ainda não entrou em depreciation. Quando entrar, <strong>D&amp;A vai acelerar materialmente</strong> (consistente com Ashkenazi disclosure pré-anuncio). 60% técnica = servers + networking, 40% = DC land/buildings.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Future leases not yet commenced $75.6B</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-21\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-21\">p.21</a>):</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;As of March 31, 2026, we have entered into leases primarily related to data centers that have not yet commenced with future lease payments of <strong>$75.6 billion</strong> that are not yet recorded. These leases will commence between 2026 and 2031 with non-cancelable lease terms primarily between one and 25 years.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ Pipeline de DCs <strong>fora do balance sheet ainda</strong> = $75.6B. Vai entrar progressivamente 2026-2031.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Long-term contractual commitments $232.7B (compute + energy + content)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-27\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-27\">p.27</a>):</p>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;As of March 31, 2026, expected future fixed or minimum guaranteed commitments under these agreements were <strong>$232.7 billion</strong>... energy service agreements include terms ranging from two to 20 years, with payments through 2047, and generally include take-or-pay provisions for minimum quantities of energy supply...&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Tipo</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Magnitude</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Long-term supply (technical infrastructure)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">majority</td></tr><tr><td>Energy service agreements (2-20yr, payments till 2047)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">substantial</td></tr><tr><td>Content licensing agreements</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">smaller</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$232.7B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Comparação vs AMZN forward commitments table $569B</strong>: AMZN tem comprometido mais em absoluto (inclui leases $110B + leases not yet commenced $106B + purchase obligations $104B), mas <strong>GOOGL tem $232.7B em contratos take-or-pay multi-ano</strong> — equivalente em magnitude relativa.</p>\n<h3><strong>🔥 Effective tax rate Q1 26 = 19.2% (vs 17.3% Q1 25)</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-45\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-45\">p.45</a>):</p>\n<ul><li>Tax provision: $7.2B → <strong>$14.8B (+105%)</strong></li><li>Effective rate: <strong>17.3% → 19.2% (+2pp)</strong></li><li>Driver: <strong>OECD Pillar 2 minimum tax (15% global)</strong> — Many countries implementing</li><li>Partially offset por: SBC tax benefits + discrete tax benefit de <strong>deconsolidation of Other Bets</strong> (Waymo / GFiber spinoff structure)</li><li>Forward: &quot;<strong>As more countries enact</strong> [OECD rules]...&quot; → tax rate tendência up nos próximos quarters</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Stock-based compensation +31% YoY</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-33\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-33\">p.33</a>):</p>\n<ul><li>Q1 26 SBC total: <strong>$7.2B</strong> (vs $5.5B Q1 25, +31%)</li><li>Settled in Alphabet stock: $6.5B (vs $5.3B Q1 25, +23%)</li><li>90M RSUs granted Q1 26 @ $305 weighted avg grant-date FV</li><li>282M → 321M unvested RSUs (more granted than vested)</li><li>→ SBC growth (&gt;&gt;revenue +22%) é margin headwind de longo prazo</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Ad metrics Q1 26 — Search saudável</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-41\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-41\">p.41</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Google Search &amp; other paid clicks</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+13%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Google Search &amp; other cost-per-click</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+5%</td></tr><tr><td>Google Network impressions</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">-9%</td></tr><tr><td>Google Network cost-per-impression</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+6%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ Paid clicks +13% ainda é <strong>acelerado</strong>. AI Overviews + AI Mode aparentemente não destruíram volume. Compatível com o &quot;queries all-time high&quot; do Sundar.</p>\n<h3><strong>🆕 Antitrust update Q1 26</strong></h3>\n<p>10-Q (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-29\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q#Page-29\">p.29</a>):</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Search case</strong>: final judgment <strong>December 2025</strong> — restrictions on distribution + obrigado <strong>share data</strong>. GOOGL appealed; DOJ also appealed. Status: <strong>pending</strong>.</li><li><strong>Ad Tech case</strong>: April 2025 mixed ruling (publisher tools anticompetitive, but advertiser tools NOT). Closing arguments <strong>Nov 2025</strong>, awaiting final judgment. <strong>GOOGL plans to appeal</strong>.</li><li><strong>EC self-preferencing fine $3.5B charge in Q3 2025</strong> — bank guarantees placed Q4 25 (em vez de cash payment). Appeal pending.</li><li><strong>DMA investigations</strong> (Search + Play) — preliminary findings of non-compliance March 2025</li><li><strong>Accrued fines and settlements on BS</strong>: $15.6B em Dec 25, <strong>$15.6B em Mar 26</strong> (flat — sem novos encargos em Q1)</li></ul>\n<h3>Implicações para tese (delta vs press release)</h3>\n<p>✓ <strong>Backlog $467.6B é o número correto para Alphabet total</strong> — GCP isolado é $462.3B. Press release transmitiu de forma a inflar percepção. <strong>Methodology change</strong> (inclui contratos ≤1yr) torna comparação histórica imperfeita. ✓ <strong>Wiz fechou 11-Mar-2026 por $29.5B</strong> — confirmação executada da deal anunciada em 2024. Goodwill $22.7B vai requerer impairment testing futuro. ✓ <strong>Intersect = renewable energy DC accelerator</strong> — vertical integration play. Sinaliza GOOGL acelerando capacity vs orgânico. ✓ <strong>Waymo $16B funding consumed in Q1</strong> — Other Bets loss vai acelerar. Optionality forte mas custo material agora explícito. ✓ <strong>Anthropic deal $40B formalizado em 10-Q</strong> ($10B + $30B equity derivative) — competitivo com AMZN $30B forward em Anthropic. ✓ <strong>GOOGL vendendo TPU externalmente agora</strong> = paralelo ao AMZN sinalizar venda de Trainium racks. <strong>Custom silicon virando produto B2B</strong>, não só serviço cloud. ⚠️ <strong>Effective tax rate up 2pp</strong> (OECD Pillar 2) — headwind estrutural daqui pra frente. ⚠️ <strong>SBC +31% vs revenue +22%</strong> — margin compression structural se mantém. ⚠️ <strong>$108.6B PP&amp;E &quot;not yet in service&quot;</strong> vai entrar em D&amp;A nos próximos quarters → <strong>Cloud margin 32.9% pode comprimir</strong> quando D&amp;A acelerar. ⚠️ <strong>Antitrust permanece overhang</strong>: 3 casos abertos com appeals/judgments pendentes — risk material que o mercado parece estar descontando.</p>\n<h3>Cross-implications atualizadas</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> — atualizar comparação backlog: <strong>GOOGL total = $467.6B; GCP-only = $462.3B; AWS = $364B</strong>. Methodology change qualifica gap como menos extremo do que sugerido pelo press release. Cross-link na seção AMZN.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=META\" title=\"wiki/META\">META</a> — Waymo $16B funding magnitude comparable às Other Bets de Meta. Confirma que Big Tech está tudo financiando AI infra + moonshots de forma agressiva.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — atualizar com dados de leases not yet commenced ($75.6B), assets not yet in service ($108.6B), credit derivatives DC backstop ($43.7B post-quarter). Total commitments forward GOOGL = magnitude consistente com guidance CapEx FY26 $175-185B.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> — TPU agora vendido externamente = mudança estrutural no thesis ASIC. Adicionar entrada.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Update Mai/2025 — Google I/O 2025 [[raw-md/GOOGL/2025-05-Google-IO-Main-Keynote]] + [[raw-md/GOOGL/2025-05-Google-IO-Developer-Keynote]]</h2><p>Google I/O 2025 (20-Mai-2025), main keynote + developer keynote. Lançamentos-chave:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Gemini 2.5 Pro + Flash</strong> — main models do ciclo</li><li><strong>Search AI Mode</strong> generally available (acelera adoption do AI overlay em Search)</li><li><strong>Jules</strong> (coding agent baseado em Gemini)</li><li><strong>Android XR Platform</strong> (apps + glasses) — Shahram Izadi</li><li><strong>Glasses &amp; AI</strong> — Nishtha Bhatia (product manager)</li><li><strong>DeepMind keynote</strong> com Demis Hassabis</li><li><strong>Search engineering</strong> (Liz Reid, Rajan Patel)</li></ul>\n<p>Speakers cross-section: <strong>DeepMind + Search + Android + Labs</strong> = mostra integração horizontal completa.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>🟢🟢 Investor Presentation 03-Jun-2026 — equity offering + CapEx FY26 revisado UP</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-06-03</strong> via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-06-03-Investor-Presentation\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2026-06-03-Investor-Presentation\">Alphabet Investor Presentation — June 2026, 48 slides</a>. Apresentação institucional publicada em conjunto com <strong>equity offering anunciada na mesma data</strong> (1ª equity issuance da Alphabet em anos).</p>\n<h3>🔥 Equity offering anunciada (slide 6 + 48)</h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We plan to fund our investments in a balanced way, including: strong operating cash flow, debt issuances, and <strong>today&#x27;s equity offering</strong>.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;The transaction we are announcing today represents a strategic proactive move to optimize our financial flexibility and maximize long-term shareholder value.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ <strong>Tamanho não disclosado na apresentação</strong> — registrar em update separado quando precificada/finalizada.</p>\n<p>→ <strong>Mudança histórica em capital structure</strong>: Alphabet havia (a) zerado buyback em Q1 26, (b) emitido $31B debt em Q1 + $20B em May, (c) agora emite <strong>equity</strong> = primeira vez em anos. Sinaliza CapEx escalando além do que cash flow + debt sustentavelmente cobrem.</p>\n<h3>🔥 CapEx FY26 revised UP + FY27 indicative</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th>Guide anterior</th><th>Guide atual</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>CapEx FY26</strong></td><td>$175-185B (Q4 FY25 EC, 11-Fev-2026)</td><td><strong>$180-190B</strong> (+$5B no mid-point)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>CapEx FY27</strong></td><td>&quot;será maior que FY26&quot; (Q4 FY25 EC)</td><td><strong>&quot;significant increase&quot;</strong> vs FY26 (mais específico)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;For the full-year 2026, we expect our CapEx to be in the range of $180B to $190B. And looking further ahead to 2027, we expect a significant increase in our CapEx compared to 2026.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p><strong>Trajetória CapEx 2022-2026E</strong>: $31B → $32B → $53B → $91B → <strong>$185B mid 2026E</strong> = <strong>6x em 4 anos = 80% CAGR FY22→FY26E</strong>.</p>\n<p>→ FY27 &quot;significant increase&quot; mid-point plausível <strong>$235-285B</strong> (assumindo +30-50% YoY) — sem precedente histórico em CapEx corporate.</p>\n<h3>🔥 Pro-forma debt $102B (May bond issuance $20B breakdown)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Tranche May 2026</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Tamanho</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">USD equiv</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>EUR notes</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">€9.0B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$9.6B</td></tr><tr><td>CAD notes</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">C$8.5B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$6.1B</td></tr><tr><td>JPY notes</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">¥576.5B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$3.8B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\">—</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>~$19.5B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Debt position</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Valor</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Long-term debt Q1 26 (10-Q)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$77.5B</td></tr><tr><td>+May 2026 bond issuance</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+$19.5B</td></tr><tr><td>Plus revolver/short-term</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~$5B</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Pro-forma Total Debt</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>~$102B</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;Since the end of the first quarter, we have issued approximately an additional $20B in debt, bringing our pro-forma debt balance to just over $100B across multiple currencies and markets.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ Combina com Q1 FY26 issuance ($31B em USD/GBP/CHF) = <strong>$51B em debt issuance em 5 meses</strong> (Jan-May 2026), maior streak de issuance da história Alphabet.</p>\n<h3>🔥 Cash flow run-rate revisado (TTM 1Q&#x27;26)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Métrica</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">FY25</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">TTM 1Q&#x27;26</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Operating Cash Flow</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$165B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$174B</strong> (+5.5%)</td></tr><tr><td>Revenue</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$403B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$422B</strong> (+4.7%)</td></tr><tr><td>Cash + marketable securities</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$127B</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$127B (mantido)</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ <strong>FCF math FY26E sob stress</strong>: OCF run-rate ~$180-200B (assumindo continuação +10% YoY) vs CapEx $180-190B = <strong>FCF near zero ou ligeiramente negativo</strong> em FY26. Justificativa explícita do equity offering.</p>\n<h3>🔥 Tokens 3.2 quadrilhão/mês — scale operacional unprecedented</h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;One way to measure growth is tokens... Two years ago, we were processing 9.7 trillion tokens [per month]. Today, that number has jumped to 3.2 quadrillion, a more than 300 times increase across our surfaces.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Período</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Tokens/mês</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Cresc</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Apr-2024</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">9.7T</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">base</td></tr><tr><td>Apr-2025</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~100T+</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+10x</td></tr><tr><td>Oct-2025</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">~1Q (1,000T)</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">+100x</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Apr-2026</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>3.2Q</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>+330x</strong> vs 2024</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Plus:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>8.5M+ developers</strong> building w/ Google AI tools</li><li><strong>~19B tokens/min</strong> processed across 1P APIs (vs 16B Q1 26 = <strong>+19% em ~5 semanas</strong>)</li><li><strong>375+ Cloud customers</strong> each processing &gt;1T tokens em 12 meses (vs ~150 em Q3 FY25 EC = <strong>+2.5x em 6 meses</strong>)</li></ul>\n<p>→ Cross-link: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (volume justifica capex setor); <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> (token explosion = quantification do Jevons Paradox em agentic workloads).</p>\n<h3>🔥 Gemini App MAU 900M (+125% YoY)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Período</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">MAU</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>May-2025</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">400M</td></tr><tr><td>Sep-2025</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">650M</td></tr><tr><td>Jan-2026</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">750M</td></tr><tr><td><strong>May-2026</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>900M</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ <strong>+125% em 12 meses</strong>. Paridade com ChatGPT em scale (ChatGPT ~900M MAU em May-2026 per estimativas externas). Fastest-growing product da Alphabet.</p>\n<h3>🔥 Search AI features — scale inédito</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Produto</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Monthly Active Users</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>AI Overviews in Search</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>2.5B+</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>AI Mode in Search</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>1B+</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;AI Overviews now have over 2.5 billion users each month. This means Google is delivering AI to more people than any other product in the world.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;AI Mode has revolutionized Search. Launched just a year ago, it&#x27;s already surpassed 1 billion monthly users.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ 2.5B AI Overviews ≈ <strong>80%+ of total Google Search users em algum momento mensal</strong>. AI Mode 1B em 12 meses post-launch = adoção mais rápida do que mobile shift histórico.</p>\n<h3>🔥 Cost reduction Gemini serving -78% em 2025</h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;We continue to drive tremendous efficiency gains - for example in 2025, we reduced Gemini serving costs by 78%.&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<p>→ Implicação direta: GCP Gemini API margin <strong>estruturalmente muito superior</strong> ao reportado em margem GCP (já tem o ponto da &quot;EBTIT&quot; critique de SemiAnalysis 27-May em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\">2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic</a>). <strong>-78% cost</strong> + Gemini API revenue scaling → unit economics agora <strong>significativamente positivas</strong>, mesmo descontando custos de training DeepMind que ficam em &quot;Alphabet-Level Activities&quot;.</p>\n<p>→ Drivers: TPU 8i (inference-specific), model optimizations, utilization improvements.</p>\n<h3>🔥 TPU 8t + TPU 8i — dual-chip institutional confirmation</h3>\n<blockquote><em>&quot;Dual chip approach with <strong>specialized architectures for training and serving</strong>&quot;</em></blockquote>\n<ul><li><strong>TPU8t</strong>: training-specific</li><li><strong>TPU8i</strong>: inference-specific</li></ul>\n<p>→ Já mencionado em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-04-FT-Kurian-Google-Cloud-AI-edge\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2026-04-FT-Kurian-Google-Cloud-AI-edge\">FT Apr-2026</a> e <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\" title=\"raw-md/TSM/2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\">MS Agentic 11-May</a>; aqui em formato canônico institutional.</p>\n<h3>🆕 Google AI Threat Defense — security suite integrada</h3>\n<p>Wiz ($29.5B M&amp;A Q1 26) + Gemini + CodeMender + Mandiant + SecOps integrados em <strong>produto único</strong> com brand &quot;Google AI Threat Defense&quot;.</p>\n<p>→ <strong>Anti-Microsoft &quot;Security Copilot&quot; play</strong>: Alphabet posicionando Wiz como spine de uma platform end-to-end (vs Microsoft que dilui security em sub-pacotes Defender).</p>\n<h3>🆕 AI Subscriptions pricing tiers</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Plano</th><th style=\"text-align:right\">Preço/mo</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Google AI Plus</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$7.99</td></tr><tr><td>Google AI Pro</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$19.99</td></tr><tr><td>Google AI Ultra 5x</td><td style=\"text-align:right\">$99.99</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Google AI Ultra 20x</strong></td><td style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>$199.99</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>→ <strong>Ultra 20x $199.99/mo</strong> = signal de high-end monetization emergente (paralelo a ChatGPT Pro $200/mo). Implicação ARPU mix: se 1% dos 350M subs migrar para Ultra → +$7B ARR potencial.</p>\n<h3>🆕 Operational milestones diversos</h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Nano Banana 50B+ images generated</strong> (image gen scale extraordinária)</li><li><strong>Antigravity millions of developers em 6 meses</strong> (Dec-2025 launch → Jun-2026)</li><li><strong>Internal AI dev tooling 3T+ tokens/day</strong> (0.5T Mar → 3T May = 6x em 60 dias)</li><li><strong>75% dos Cloud customers usam AI products</strong> (1ª disclosure)</li><li><strong>Q1 26 deal velocity</strong>: 2x customer acquisition + 2x deals $100M-$1B+ YoY</li><li><strong>YouTube 13.2% US TV watch share</strong> (Nielsen Mar-2026, vs 12.0% Mar-2025)</li><li><strong>Waymo 11 US cities, 6 launched in 2026, international expansion soon</strong> (Q1 26 mencionou 500K+ rides/week; aqui detalha geografia)</li><li><strong>Wing 1M+ home deliveries</strong> (Walmart + DoorDash partnerships)</li><li><strong>Universal Commerce Protocol</strong> — open-source spec co-developed com retailers</li></ul>\n<h3>Implicações para tese (delta vs Q1 FY26 10-Q em 07-May)</h3>\n<p>✓ <strong>CapEx revised UP (+$5B mid)</strong> valida thesis &quot;demand &gt; supply&quot; — Ashkenazi (Mar-2026) já flagava elasticity ao alto. Confirmado. ✓ <strong>Equity offering hoje</strong> + debt $20B May = capital structure pivotando para suportar ramp acelerado. <strong>Sinal forte de conviction interno</strong>. ✓ <strong>Tokens 3.2Q/mês + 19B/min via 1P API</strong> = scale operacional <strong>2-3 ordens de magnitude</strong> acima de qualquer outro player. ✓ <strong>Gemini App 900M MAU</strong> = paridade com ChatGPT em escala, ganhando narrative. ✓ <strong>AI Overviews 2.5B + AI Mode 1B MAU</strong> = Search <strong>NÃO</strong> é vítima de AI threat — é o <strong>maior beneficiário</strong> em delivery. ✓ <strong>Cost serving -78%</strong> = unit economics Gemini API estruturalmente positivas (mesmo descontando training cost em outros segments). ⚠️ <strong>CapEx FY27 &quot;significant increase&quot;</strong> = se +50% YoY = $280B+. <strong>FCF negativo material em FY27</strong> se OCF não acelerar materialmente. Equity offering hoje pode ser <strong>1ª de várias</strong>. ⚠️ <strong>Equity dilution</strong>: tamanho não anunciado na apresentação. Material a confirmar nos próximos dias quando precificar. ⚠️ <strong>FCF math FY26</strong>: OCF run-rate $180-200B vs CapEx $180-190B + M&amp;A + Waymo $16B + dividend = <strong>FCF zero ou negativo</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Cross-implications atualizadas</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> — comparação CapEx hyperscalers FY26E: GOOGL <strong>$185B</strong> vs AMZN (~$140-160B sell-side), MSFT (~$120-130B). GOOGL agora <strong>líder de CapEx em magnitude absoluta</strong>.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> — 1.3M NVDA GPUs em Google é ratificado por TPU 8t/8i dual-chip = <strong>multi-vendor strategy sustained</strong>. NVDA exposure GOOGL crescendo apesar de TPU custom.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> — TPU 8 generation = ramp continuing partnership. Broadcom design partner.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=MU\" title=\"wiki/MU\">MU</a> — HBM demand para TPU 8t/8i = Micron como supplier indireto via AVGO partnership.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> — atualizar com $180-190B FY26E + indicative FY27 &quot;significant increase&quot; + first-ever equity offering como funding source. <strong>Setor hyperscaler CapEx CY26 = &gt;$800B annual run rate</strong> (GOOGL $185 + AMZN $150 + MSFT $130 + META $130 + ORCL $40 + OCI/neoclouds).</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> — TPU 8t/8i dual-chip institutionally confirmed = arquitetural divergence training vs inference proliferando (paralelo a NVDA Vera+Rubin training / B100/B200 inference).</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=harness-as-moat\" title=\"_concepts/harness-as-moat\">harness-as-moat</a> — Antigravity millions of developers em 6 meses + 3T tokens/day internal = harness GOOGL platform play se materializando.</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> — 3.2Q tokens/mês = quantification do volume explosion driver agentic.</li></ul></section>\n<details class=\"notes-appendix\"><summary>Notas, pendências e changelog</summary><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Pontos em aberto</h2><ul><li>[x] ~~10-K FY25 + earnings calls FY25: SEC EDGAR download pendente~~ — <strong>5 10-Ks FY21-FY25 OCR&#x27;d em 27-Apr-2026</strong></li><li>[x] ~~1 PDF status NEEDS_OCR~~ — initiate-outperform-AI-mode OCR&#x27;d 2026-04-23</li><li>[x] ~~GCP operating margin~~ — disclosed nos 10-Ks: FY23 5,2% / FY24 14,1% / FY25 23,7%</li><li>[ ] Earnings calls FY25 (Q1-Q4) — ainda não no vault</li><li>[ ] Antitrust remedies final — decisão final provavelmente 2026.</li><li>[ ] Waymo scale trajectory — rides/day evolution.</li><li>[ ] CapEx breakdown FY25 (servers vs data center vs network) — comparar com $185bn FY26E forecast.</li><li>[ ] Anthropic $40bn deal — termos detalhados (equity vs commitment vs convertible).</li><li>[ ] Rodar Perguntas 1-4 para GOOGL com base histórica agora disponível.</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Histórico de atualizações</h2><ul><li><strong>2026-06-04</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/AVGO/FY26-Q2-earnings-call\">AVGO Q2 FY26 EC, 03-Jun-2026</a>. <strong>Datapoints GOOGL-side</strong>: (1) Hock Tan confirma <strong>April 2026 long-term agreement</strong> com Google para &quot;<strong>multiple generations of TPUs and AI networking</strong>&quot; — formaliza institucionalmente o framing histórico &quot;Google = AVGO maior cliente ASIC&quot;; (2) <strong>Anthropic compute capacity disclosure detalhada</strong>: 1GW TPU-based em 2026 (existing) + <strong>5GW next-generation TPU-based compute beginning 2027</strong> (April 2026 agreement) — triangulação confirmed GOOGL ($40B Anthropic deal) ↔ Anthropic (end customer) ↔ AVGO (silicon supplier); (3) <strong>TPU 8t (training) + TPU 8i (inference)</strong> confirmados como dual-chip institutional (mesma estrutura que GOOGL disclosed em Investor Presentation 03-Jun); (4) <strong>Tomahawk 7 (200T) Ethernet switch taping out this quarter</strong> — AVGO networking continua roadmap paralelo ao TPU ramp GCP; (5) <strong>🆕 AI XPV Platform $35B Apollo 1ª tranche</strong> — vendor financing externalizado para Anthropic + OpenAI fora do framework GCP/AWS/Azure tradicional. Implicação GOOGL: AVGO confirma que Anthropic compra silicon TPU-based (não só compute via GCP) — paralelo ao SemiAnalysis EBTIT critique (27-May) sobre royalty TPU vendido externamente. Hock corrigiu Tom O&#x27;Malley: AVGO <strong>NÃO é &quot;backstop&quot;</strong> do deal Anthropic, é o <strong>chip supplier direto</strong>. <strong>Implicação central</strong>: GCP é o cloud/IP integrator + Apollo/Blackstone são os financiadores externalizados + AVGO é o silicon vendor. Stack triangular formalizado por 1ª vez em earnings call. Cross-link <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> seção &quot;Q2 FY26 EC&quot;.</li><li><strong>2026-06-03</strong>: 🟢🟢 <strong>Alphabet Investor Presentation — June 2026 ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-06-03-Investor-Presentation\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2026-06-03-Investor-Presentation\">2026-06-03-Investor-Presentation</a> — 48 slides, anexada pelo Paulo, extração manual no formato canônico). Adicionada nova seção &quot;Investor Presentation 03-Jun-2026 — equity offering + CapEx FY26 revisado UP&quot;. <strong>Disclosures centrais</strong>: (1) <strong>🔥 Equity offering anunciada hoje</strong> (1ª equity issuance Alphabet em anos, tamanho não disclosado na apresentação); (2) <strong>🔥 CapEx FY26 revised UP</strong>: $175-185B → <strong>$180-190B</strong> (+$5B mid); (3) <strong>🔥 CapEx FY27 indicative</strong>: &quot;significant increase&quot; vs FY26 (plausível $235-285B se +30-50% YoY); (4) <strong>Pro-forma debt $102B</strong> = $77.5B Q1 26 + <strong>~$20B May 2026 bond issuance</strong> em €9B + C$8.5B + ¥576.5B; (5) <strong>TTM 1Q&#x27;26 Revenue $422B</strong> (+$63B YoY) + <strong>OCF $174B</strong>; (6) <strong>🔥 Tokens 3.2Q/mês</strong> (vs 9.7T Apr-2024 = <strong>330x em 2 anos</strong>); (7) <strong>~19B tokens/min via 1P APIs</strong> (vs 16B Q1 26 = +19% em 5 sem); (8) <strong>375+ Cloud customers &gt;1T tokens/yr</strong> (vs ~150 Q3 FY25 = 2.5x); (9) <strong>8.5M+ developers</strong> com Google AI tools; (10) <strong>Gemini App 900M MAU as of May-2026</strong> (vs 400M May-25 = 2.25x YoY); (11) <strong>AI Overviews 2.5B+ MAU</strong> (1ª disclosure exata); (12) <strong>AI Mode 1B+ MAU</strong> (consistente Q1 EC); (13) <strong>🔥 Gemini serving cost -78% em 2025</strong> — implicação Gemini API margin estruturalmente positivas; (14) <strong>TPU 8t (training) + TPU 8i (inference)</strong> dual-chip institutional confirmation; (15) <strong>🆕 Google AI Threat Defense</strong> brand (Wiz + Gemini + CodeMender + Mandiant + SecOps); (16) <strong>AI subscription pricing tiers</strong> $7.99/$19.99/$99.99/<strong>$199.99</strong>/mo (Ultra 20x = high-end monetization); (17) <strong>Nano Banana 50B+ images</strong> generated; (18) <strong>Antigravity millions of developers em 6 meses</strong>; (19) <strong>Internal AI dev tooling 3T+ tokens/day</strong> (0.5T Mar → 3T May = <strong>6x em 60 dias</strong>); (20) <strong>75% dos Cloud customers usam AI products</strong> (1ª disclosure); (21) <strong>Q1 26 deal velocity 2x YoY</strong> customer acquisition + 2x $100M-$1B+ deals; (22) <strong>YouTube 13.2% US TV watch share Mar-2026</strong> (vs 12.0% Mar-2025); (23) <strong>Waymo 11 US cities + 6 launched 2026 + intl expansion soon</strong> (sobre 500K+ rides/week já no Q1 26); (24) <strong>Wing 1M+ home deliveries</strong> Walmart/DoorDash; (25) <strong>Universal Commerce Protocol</strong> open-source spec co-developed com retailers. <strong>Cross-implications</strong>: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> atualizado (GOOGL $185B mid = líder absoluto CapEx; setor agregado &gt;$800B annual run rate CY26), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> (3.2Q tokens/mês quantifica Jevons em agentic), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=harness-as-moat\" title=\"_concepts/harness-as-moat\">harness-as-moat</a> (Antigravity millions devs + 3T int tokens/day), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> (dual-chip TPU 8t/8i = training vs inference architectural divergence). <strong>Implicação central</strong>: a apresentação é a <strong>justificativa institucional do equity offering</strong> — primeira vez que Alphabet usa equity para financiar CapEx, indicando que <strong>CapEx &gt; OCF sustainability</strong> vai requerer mais issuances futuras (FY27 &quot;significant increase&quot; + FCF math near zero FY26).</li><li><strong>2026-04-21</strong>: wiki criada a partir da Fase 1 (6 PDFs — 3 Paulo internal + JPM Jul/2025 + 1 NEEDS_OCR + antitrust filing). Baseada majoritariamente em Paulo&#x27;s 2024-recap (framework Pergunta 1-4) + general knowledge.</li><li><strong>2026-04-23</strong>: initiate-outperform-AI-mode.md destravado via rapidocr-onnxruntime (status NEEDS_OCR removido).</li><li><strong>2026-04-27</strong>: <strong>Fase 2 ingestão</strong> — 5 10-Ks históricos FY21/FY22/FY23/FY24/FY25 convertidos via OCR. Adicionada seção &quot;Evolução histórica FY20 → FY25&quot; com revenue por segmento + OP por segmento + GCP margin trajectory. <strong>Insights novos</strong>: (a) revenue total FY25 $402,8bn (+15%) — antes inexistente no vault; (b) <strong>GCP $58,7bn (+36%) com OP $13,9bn margin 23,7%</strong> — inflexão clara; (c) Google Network em declínio estrutural (-2%); (d) Mix shift Cloud +3,8pp em 2 anos. Também ingerido FT article 26-Apr-2026 (Kurian) com guidance FY26E GCP &gt;$70bn, CapEx $185bn, Anthropic deal $40bn, e Epoch AI compute share data.</li><li><strong>2026-05-07</strong> (later): ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 10-Q ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">FY26-Q1-10-Q</a> — 54 páginas, OCR&#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime, PDF tinha text layer mas com font encoding scrambled). Adicionada seção &quot;Q1 FY26 10-Q — disclosures novas vs press release&quot;. <strong>Disclosures NÃO cobertos no press release</strong>: (1) <strong>Backlog total $467.6B</strong> (vs $462.3B Cloud-only) — methodology change inclui contratos ≤1yr daqui pra frente; (2) <strong>Wiz acquisition closed 11-Mar-2026 por $29.5B</strong> ($22.7B goodwill GCP + $8.3B intangibles); (3) <strong>🆕 Intersect renewable energy acquisition closed 10-Mar-2026 por $5.9B</strong> — DC capacity acceleration play; (4) <strong>🆕 GFiber pending divestiture</strong> ($1.5B cash + $2B note + 49.99% equity); (5) <strong>🆕 Waymo recebeu $16.0B funding em Fev/2026</strong> (&quot;significant majority&quot; Alphabet) — magnitude que justifica Other Bets loss -$2.1B; (6) <strong>Anthropic deal $40B formalizado</strong> ($10B direct + $30B equity derivative contingent em milestones até 2030); (7) <strong>🆕 TPU sendo vendido externamente</strong> (&quot;limited number of agreements to supply TPU hardware to customers... on-premises infrastructure&quot;) — paralelo ao AMZN com Trainium racks; (8) <strong>Long-term debt issuance Q1 26 = $31.1B</strong> em 3 currencies (USD $20B 4.80% 15y / GBP £5.5B 5.31% 31y / CHF 3.1B 1.06% 10y); (9) <strong>Credit derivatives notional $28.4B Q1 + $15.3B post-quarter abril = $43.7B</strong> em DC backstops; (10) <strong>PP&amp;E &quot;assets NOT yet in service&quot; +$30B QoQ para $108.6B</strong> — D&amp;A vai acelerar materialmente próximos quarters; (11) <strong>Future leases not yet commenced $75.6B</strong> (DCs, 2026-2031); (12) <strong>Long-term contractual commitments $232.7B</strong> (energy take-or-pay até 2047 + supply); (13) <strong>Effective tax rate 17.3% → 19.2%</strong> (OECD Pillar 2 driver, partial offset SBC + Other Bets deconsolidation); (14) <strong>SBC $7.2B (+31% YoY)</strong> vs revenue +22% = margin compression sustained; (15) <strong>Search paid clicks +13% YoY</strong> + cost-per-click +5% — Search saudável apesar AI threat; (16) <strong>Antitrust</strong>: Search appeal pending (final judgment Dec 2025), Ad Tech awaiting judgment, EC fine $3.5B em Q3 25 (bank guarantees em Q4), DMA preliminary non-compliance findings — risk material em aberto. Cross-implications atualizadas: AMZN (correct backlog comparison), META (Waymo $16B funding context), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (forward visibility commitments), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> (TPU virando B2B). <strong>Implicação central</strong>: 10-Q reforça narrativa positiva do press release <strong>mas qualifica</strong> com (a) backlog methodology change + (b) tax rate stepping up + (c) Other Bets/Waymo cost ramping + (d) D&amp;A acceleration coming.</li><li><strong>2026-05-07</strong>: ✅ <strong>Q1 FY26 press release ingerido</strong> (<a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-press-release\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-press-release\">FY26-Q1-press-release</a> — release date 29-Apr-2026, period ended 31-Mar-2026, PDF text-based — sem OCR). Adicionada nova seção &quot;Q1 FY26 — primeiro reality check pós-FY25&quot;. <strong>Disclosures materiais</strong>: (1) <strong>Total revenue $109.9B (+22%, +19% cc)</strong> — 11º trimestre consecutivo de double-digit growth; (2) <strong>Cloud +63% YoY = 5ª aceleração trimestral consecutiva</strong> (+28→+32→+34→+48→+63); (3) <strong>Cloud backlog $460B+ — quase dobrou QoQ ($240B → $460B), ULTRAPASSOU AWS pela 1ª vez</strong> (AWS Q1 26 = $364B); (4) <strong>Cloud margin 32.9%</strong> (vs 30.1% Q4 25, 23.7% FY25) — em paridade com AWS em margem; (5) <strong>Search +19% YoY</strong> — queries all-time high, &quot;AI experiences driving usage&quot; (validates AI Mode tese de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=initiate-outperform-AI-mode\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/initiate-outperform-AI-mode\">initiate-outperform-AI-mode</a>); (6) <strong>350M paid subscriptions</strong> (vs 300M Q3 25, 270M Q1 25 = +30% em 12mo); (7) <strong>Gemini Enterprise paid MAU +40% QoQ</strong>; (8) <strong>Gemini API &gt;16B tokens/min, +60% QoQ</strong>; (9) <strong>Waymo &gt;500K fully autonomous rides/week</strong> (de ~250K Q3 25 = 2x em 6 meses); (10) <strong>EPS reportado $5.11 (+82%) inclui $2.35 de equity gain não-recorrente</strong> ($36.9B equity sec mark-up Anthropic + outros) → Operating EPS Q1 26 ~$2.76 (-2% YoY); (11) <strong>Non-marketable securities +$38B QoQ</strong> ($68.7B → $106.9B) — equity stakes em AI labs marcando para cima; (12) <strong>CapEx Q1 26 $35.7B (+107% YoY)</strong> — run-rate $143B vs guidance $175-185B FY26 = aceleração esperada nos Q2-Q4; (13) <strong>Buyback ZERO em Q1</strong> (vs $15B Q1 25) — capital allocation 100% pra AI infra + M&amp;A; (14) <strong>M&amp;A $33.6B + Goodwill +$24B</strong> = closing da aquisição Wiz ($32B); (15) <strong>Bond issuance $31.1B em Q1</strong> — long-term debt $46.5B → $77.5B (+$31B), paralelo ao AMZN ($53.8B); (16) <strong>Dividend +5% para $0.22/share</strong> (anunciado 27-Apr-2026); (17) <strong>Other Bets loss -$2.1B + Alphabet shared R&amp;D -$5.4B = $7.5B drag/Q vs $4.3B Q1 25</strong>. Cross-implications: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> (GCP backlog &gt; AWS pela 1ª vez), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> (TPU demand sustentada), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=NVDA\" title=\"wiki/NVDA\">NVDA</a> (multi-vendor accelerator confirmation), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (CapEx setor &gt;$700B annual run rate), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a> (TPU stack +63% growth = data point estrutural). <strong>Implicação central</strong>: Cloud virou o crown jewel da Alphabet — backlog ultrapassando AWS é o primeiro hard data point que valida estruturalmente a tese &quot;GCP closing gap via AI&quot; (Kurian disclosure 8 anos).</li><li><strong>2026-04-27 (later)</strong>: <strong>Fase 2 transcripts</strong> — 8 transcripts ingested via OCR (4 earnings calls FY25 + 2 Google I/O 2025 + GS Communacopia + MS TMT). Adicionadas 4 novas seções na wiki: &quot;FY25 trimestral&quot;, &quot;Update Set/2025 Kurian&quot;, &quot;Update Mar/2026 Ashkenazi&quot;, &quot;Update Mai/2025 Google I/O&quot;. <strong>Insights novos</strong>: (a) <strong>CapEx FY26 confirmado $175-185bn</strong> (vs $91bn FY25 actual, <strong>2x increase</strong>); (b) <strong>Cloud backlog $240bn end Q4 FY25</strong> (+55% QoQ, &gt;2x YoY); (c) <strong>Apple = preferred cloud provider</strong>, develop next-gen Apple Foundation Models on Gemini; (d) <strong>120k+ enterprises usando Gemini</strong>, 95% top 20 SaaS, 80% top 100 SaaS; (e) <strong>Q4 GenAI revenue +400%</strong>, accelerating from Q3 +200%; (f) Kurian disclosure: TPUs com <strong>2x power efficiency, 50% performance delta</strong> vs concorrentes; (g) Ashkenazi disclosure: <strong>demand &gt; supply em Cloud por múltiplos quarters</strong>. Total docs GOOGL: <strong>20</strong> (era 12).</li><li><strong>2026-05-19</strong>: ingerido <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\" title=\"raw-md/TSM/2026-05-11-MS-Agentic-AI-Surge\">Morgan Stanley &amp;quot;Agentic AI — The Surge Begins&amp;quot; 11-May-2026</a>. Confirma <strong>Google Cloud +63% YoY US$20.0bn 1Q26</strong> e adiciona o posicionamento agentic explícito: <strong>Gemini Enterprise Agent Platform</strong> (camada de conexão p/ build/deploy/manage de agents), <strong>Agentic Data Cloud</strong>, <strong>US$750mn comprometido</strong> ao ecossistema de <strong>120k membros</strong>, e novo hardware <strong>TPU 8t / 8i</strong> desenhado para workloads agentic. Reforça a tese &quot;GCP closing gap via AI&quot; e a leitura de <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=agentic-AI-CPU-shift\" title=\"_concepts/agentic-AI-CPU-shift\">agentic-AI-CPU-shift</a> / <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (CapEx indo também p/ silício+plataforma agentic).</li><li><strong>2026-05-27</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\" title=\"raw-md/AMZN/2026-05-27-semianalysis-aws-bedrock-anthropic\">SemiAnalysis &amp;quot;Anthropic Growth and Bedrock Mix Drive AWS Margins Higher&amp;quot; 27-May-2026</a> (arquivado em AMZN; leitura comparativa <strong>crítica</strong> sobre GCP). <strong>Datapoints GOOGL-side</strong>: (1) <strong>Critique central</strong>: a margem GCP é uma &quot;<strong>EBTIT</strong> — Earnings Before Training, Interest and Taxes&quot; margin. Custos de DeepMind/Gemini training estão contabilizados em &quot;<strong>Alphabet-Level Activities</strong>&quot;, não em GCP. Per Alphabet 10-Q 1Q26: Alphabet-Level Activities &quot;primarily reflect expenses related to our shared AI research and development&quot; = <strong>US$5,4B (1Q26) vs US$3,0B (1Q25), +80% YoY</strong>. → Toda receita Gemini API flui para GCP a margens above average, enquanto <strong>US$10B+/ano em run-rate cost</strong> ficam em outro segmento. <strong>Margem GCP reportada está estruturalmente inflada vs peers que carregam treino dentro da unidade cloud</strong>. (2) <strong>TPU vendido externamente à Anthropic via Broadcom</strong> — Google atuando como <strong>IP vendor</strong> pode ter beneficiado a margem GCP via <strong>royalty payments one-off</strong> (não estrutural). Combina com disclose anterior do 10-Q Q1 FY26 GOOGL (&quot;limited number of agreements to supply TPU hardware to customers... on-premises infrastructure&quot;). (3) <strong>Capacity constraint global</strong>: SemiAnalysis aponta que Google é &quot;the ultimate supply-constrained business&quot; — compete simultaneamente com AWS (cloud), NVDA (hardware), Anthropic/OpenAI (modelos), Meta (ads), Tesla (FSD). Capacity interna não cresce suficiente pra servir tudo. <strong>Gemini Enterprise Agent Platform (ex-Vertex) está vendo adições de capacidade significativamente menores que Bedrock</strong>. (4) <strong>GCP como upsell platform</strong>: SemiAnalysis caracteriza GCP como plataforma pra upsell adicional. Exemplo paradigmático = Meta: primeiro deal GPU → adoção em larga escala Gemini → deal massivo TPU hardware. (5) <strong>TaaS Run-Rate Revenue ranking</strong>: Bedrock &gt; Gemini API &gt; Azure Foundry &gt; Oracle + neoclouds ~zero. Gemini API ficou #2 do mercado TaaS, mas em segundo lugar atrás do Bedrock. (6) Margin GCP no quadro &quot;Q/Q delta 1Q26&quot; aparece <strong>ligeiramente negativa</strong>, não positiva (contradição com headline +60% growth — explicada justamente pelo EBTIT). <strong>Implicação</strong>: tese GCP &quot;closing gap&quot; continua válida em revenue + backlog (já capturado nas update 27-Apr e 07-May), mas <strong>margin profile do GCP é overstated</strong> — investidor que olha margem GCP isolada está subestimando o custo real de servir esse revenue. <strong>Cross-link</strong>: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AMZN\" title=\"wiki/AMZN\">AMZN</a> (contraponto: AWS carrega tudo dentro da unidade cloud), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">AVGO</a> (Broadcom como IP vendor/canal para TPU-Anthropic), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=harness-as-moat\" title=\"_concepts/harness-as-moat\">harness-as-moat</a> (Gemini API &lt; Bedrock em TaaS economics), <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=hyperscaler-capex\" title=\"_concepts/hyperscaler-capex\">hyperscaler-capex</a> (Google supply-constrained vs AWS lighting speed).</li><li><strong>2026-05-25</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-05-22-uncoveralpha-harness-moat\" title=\"raw-md/MSFT/2026-05-22-uncoveralpha-harness-moat\">UncoverAlpha &amp;quot;Harness as Moat&amp;quot; 22-May-2026</a> (arquivado sob MSFT por ser o foco do investment angle do autor, mas toca GOOGL). <strong>Implicações p/ Alphabet</strong>: (1) <strong>Google deprecated Gemini CLI e substituiu por Antigravity CLI</strong> — server-side harness <strong>unificado</strong> com o <strong>Antigravity desktop IDE</strong> (sinal de comoditização do CLI standalone e foco no matched-pair model+harness); (2) Antigravity é o exemplo paradigmático de <strong>lab que possui ambos lados do par</strong> (Gemini + harness próprio), construindo o tipo de platform lock-in que historicamente produziu high-margin businesses (analogia explícita Microsoft 1990s); (3) <strong>Antigravity abriu harness pra Claude models</strong> — movimento simétrico ao do MSFT (Copilot CLI multi-modelo), mas a partir do lado que TEM frontier model; (4) <strong>Risco</strong>: IDE adoption ainda atrás de VS Code/Cursor — Antigravity positioned p/ parallel-agent future que pode estar mais longe do que o marketing implica; (5) <strong>Upside</strong>: se agentic development virar default paradigm em 2027-2028, stack vertical <strong>TPU → Gemini → Antigravity → Cloud</strong> = &quot;um dos end-to-end AI platforms mais limpos do mercado&quot; (UncoverAlpha). Conceito novo: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=harness-as-moat\" title=\"_concepts/harness-as-moat\">harness-as-moat</a>. Autor declara posição em GOOGL. Datapoint do moat: harness sozinho move +13.7pp em Terminal-Bench 2.0 (LangChain) vs +6.8pp de upgrade de geração (Claude 4.5→4.7).</li><li><strong>2026-05-20</strong>: cross-ref <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY27-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/NVDA/FY27-Q1-earnings-call\">NVDA Q1 FY27 earnings call, 20-May-2026</a>. Disclosures Google-side: (1) <strong>Blackwell na cloud GCP com confidential computing</strong> (&quot;new foundation for secure, high-performance AI&quot; — capability inédita); (2) <strong>A5X bare metal instances</strong> suportando <strong>até 960,000 Rubin GPUs across multiple sites</strong> — Google = early adopter de Vera Rubin (shipments Q3 FY27); (3) Anthropic deal já formalizado (ver Histórico 07-May) ganha contexto: NVDA suporta capacity Anthropic via AWS/Azure/CoreWeave/Space xAI — GCP é base mas multi-cloud. Implicação: GCP <strong>acoplada estruturalmente</strong> com NVDA (apesar TPU 8t/8i interno) — confirma coexistência ASIC+GPU em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=ASIC-vs-GPU\" title=\"_concepts/ASIC-vs-GPU\">ASIC-vs-GPU</a>; e A5X = compromisso de <strong>escala inédita</strong> (960k Rubins cross-sites). Cross-link: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=Vera-Rubin\" title=\"_concepts/Vera-Rubin\">Vera-Rubin</a>.</li></ul></section><section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Fontes no vault</h2><h3>SEC Filings (10-Ks) — <em>ingested 2026-04-27</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY21-10-K\">FY21-10-K</a> — boom pandêmico (221 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY22-10-K\">FY22-10-K</a> — ads recession (214 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a> — cost discipline year (222 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a> — re-acceleração + AI gear-up (236 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a> — GCP $58,7bn / +36% / OP margin 23,7% (242 KB)</li></ul>\n<h3>Earnings Calls (FactSet Final Transcripts) — <em>ingested 2026-04-27</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-Q1-earnings-call\">FY25-Q1-earnings-call</a> — Apr-2025 (46 KB) — Cloud Next, AI leadership stance</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-Q2-earnings-call\">FY25-Q2-earnings-call</a> — Jul-2025 (48 KB) — Cloud run rate &gt;$50bn; Gemini +35x YoY</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-Q3-earnings-call\">FY25-Q3-earnings-call</a> — Oct-2025 (45 KB) — Backlog $155bn (+46% QoQ); &gt;$1bn deals trump 2y combined</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-Q4-earnings-call\">FY25-Q4-earnings-call</a> — Feb-2026 (52 KB) — <strong>CapEx FY26 $175-185bn</strong>; Backlog $240bn; Apple deal; Cloud +48%</li></ul>\n<h3>Press Releases — <em>ingested 2026-05-07</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-press-release\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-press-release\">FY26-Q1-press-release</a> — Q1 FY26 (29-Apr-2026) — <strong>Cloud +63%, backlog $460B (&gt;AWS), margin 32.9%, 350M subs, Waymo 500K+ rides/week</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>SEC Filings (10-Q) — <em>ingested 2026-05-07</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY26-Q1-10-Q\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY26-Q1-10-Q\">FY26-Q1-10-Q</a> — Q1 FY26 (period ended 31-Mar-2026, filed Apr-2026) — <strong>Total backlog $467.6B (Cloud $462.3B), Wiz closed $29.5B, Intersect $5.9B, Waymo $16B funding, Anthropic $40B formalizado, TPU vendendo externamente, $31B bond issuance 3 currencies</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>Eventos &amp; Conferências — <em>ingested 2026-04-27 / 2026-06-03</em></h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-05-Google-IO-Main-Keynote\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2025-05-Google-IO-Main-Keynote\">2025-05-Google-IO-Main-Keynote</a> — Gemini 2.5 + Search AI Mode + Android XR (68 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-05-Google-IO-Developer-Keynote\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2025-05-Google-IO-Developer-Keynote\">2025-05-Google-IO-Developer-Keynote</a> — Gemini 2.5 Pro/Flash + Jules (49 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-09-GS-Communacopia-Kurian\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2025-09-GS-Communacopia-Kurian\">2025-09-GS-Communacopia-Kurian</a> — TPU 11y history; 9 of 10 AI labs (26 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-03-MS-TMT-Ashkenazi\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2026-03-MS-TMT-Ashkenazi\">2026-03-MS-TMT-Ashkenazi</a> — CapEx framework, demand &gt; supply (33 KB)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-06-03-Investor-Presentation\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2026-06-03-Investor-Presentation\">2026-06-03-Investor-Presentation</a> — <strong>Investor Presentation Jun-2026 (48 slides) — equity offering anunciada + CapEx FY26 revised $180-190B + tokens 3.2Q/mês + Gemini App 900M MAU</strong></li></ul>\n<h3>Documentos internos do Paulo</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=paulo-memo\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/paulo-memo\">paulo-memo</a> — memo interno</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=paulo-ppt\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/paulo-ppt\">paulo-ppt</a> — PPT interno (40K chars, análise mais extensa)</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2024-recap\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2024-recap\">2024-recap</a> — recap 2024 (framework Pergunta 1-4)</li></ul>\n<h3>Research</h3>\n<ul><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-07-JPM-latest\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2025-07-JPM-latest\">2025-07-JPM-latest</a> — JPM Jul/2025</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=initiate-outperform-AI-mode\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/initiate-outperform-AI-mode\">initiate-outperform-AI-mode</a> — ✓ OCR&#x27;d 2026-04-23</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=antitrust-final-remedies\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/antitrust-final-remedies\">antitrust-final-remedies</a> — DOJ filing, remedies finais Search case</li><li><a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2026-04-FT-Kurian-Google-Cloud-AI-edge\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2026-04-FT-Kurian-Google-Cloud-AI-edge\">2026-04-FT-Kurian-Google-Cloud-AI-edge</a> — <em>ingested 2026-04-27</em> — FT entrevista com Kurian; TPU 8ª geração, Anthropic $40bn deal, CapEx $185bn FY26E</li></ul>\n<h3>Backlog</h3>\n<ul><li>BofA Alphabet + Waymo reports — Fase 2</li><li>Google Reshapes Search Around — Fase 2</li><li>googl.bmo.pdf — Fase 2</li><li>2018 Alphabet Investor Relations — Fase 2 (stale)</li></ul></section></details>", "ic": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Tese de investimento (resumo — framework Paulo recap 2024)</h2><p><strong>Segmentos CY2024 (do recap Paulo):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>CY2023 ($M)</th><th>CY2024 ($M)</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Search</td><td>175,033</td><td>198,084</td><td>+13.2%</td></tr><tr><td>YouTube Ads</td><td>31,510</td><td>36,147</td><td>+14.7%</td></tr><tr><td>Network members</td><td>31,312</td><td>30,359</td><td>-3.0%</td></tr><tr><td>Google Other</td><td>34,688</td><td>40,340</td><td>+16.3%</td></tr><tr><td>GCP</td><td>33,088</td><td>43,229</td><td>+30.7%</td></tr><tr><td>Other Bets</td><td>1,527</td><td>1,648</td><td>+7.9%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Gross Revenue</strong></td><td><strong>307,394</strong></td><td><strong>350,018</strong></td><td><strong>+13.9%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Key financials CY2024:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Gross Revenue: $350B (+13.9%)</li><li>Net Revenue: $295B</li><li>Gross margin: 58.2%</li><li><strong>EBIT margin: 32.1%</strong> (up from 27.4% FY23 → <strong>+522 bps</strong>)</li><li>Net income: ~$100B</li><li>FCF net of SBC: growing</li></ul>\n<p><strong>10-year track record (2014-2024):</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Net revenue CAGR: 18.2%</li><li>EBIT margin: 25% → 32% (expanding)</li><li>ROIC: 33% (2024) — estrutural high</li><li>Share count: trending down via buybacks</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Triggers / bull case:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>GCP accelerando (+31% YoY 2024) — diferente de Azure em trajetória similar</li><li>YouTube Shorts $50B+ ARR  </li><li>TPU moat — ASIC próprio maduro (v7p Ironwood) via <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=AVGO\" title=\"wiki/AVGO\">Broadcom</a> partnership</li><li>Waymo escalando (Other Bets) — robotaxi</li><li>AI Mode em Search staunching share losses vs ChatGPT/Perplexity (research <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=initiate-outperform-AI-mode\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/initiate-outperform-AI-mode\">initiate-outperform-AI-mode</a>)</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Riscos / bear case:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>Antitrust (US)</strong>: Google search monopoly case — remedies propostos Jul/2025 em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=antitrust-final-remedies\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/antitrust-final-remedies\">antitrust-final-remedies</a> (DOJ quer forçar divestiture de Chrome / separar ad stack). Risco existencial pro moat.</li><li><strong>Search disruption</strong>: ChatGPT/Perplexity/Claude erodindo query volume (Search queries ainda cresce, mas slower que web generally).</li><li><strong>Capex</strong>: GCP + Gemini + TPUs consumindo ~$75B FY25E.</li><li><strong>Gemini monetization</strong>: ainda sem revenue model standalone.</li></ul></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Riscos — Antitrust detalhado</h2><p><strong>DOJ vs Google (Search)</strong> — case já perdido. Remedies propostos Jul/2025:</p>\n<ul><li>Forçar <strong>divestiture de Chrome</strong> (DOJ pedido) — bloqueia default search deal com Apple</li><li><strong>Separar ad stack</strong> (AdSense + AdX + DV360)</li><li>Obrigar <strong>partilhar search index/data</strong></li></ul>\n<p>Se remedies vingarem completos: moat de Search pode ser permanentemente impaired. Paulo&#x27;s view precisa incorporar cenário. Material em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=antitrust-final-remedies\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/antitrust-final-remedies\">antitrust-final-remedies</a> (DOJ filing) e <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=paulo-ppt\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/paulo-ppt\">paulo-ppt</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>EU</strong>: DMA compliance, GDPR.</p></section>", "val": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Valuation</h2><ul><li><strong>[ ] Pergunta 4 pendente.</strong></li><li>Research em <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=2025-07-JPM-latest\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/2025-07-JPM-latest\">2025-07-JPM-latest</a> tem JPM latest estimate (Jul/2025) com target e números atualizados.</li></ul></section>", "pa": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Historical Price Action</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/GOOGL.md</code>.</p></div>", "er": "<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>Evolução histórica — retrospectiva FY20 → FY25</h2><p>Adicionada <strong>2026-04-27</strong> via ingestão de 5 10-Ks SEC FY21-FY25 (OCR&#x27;d via rapidocr-onnxruntime). Fontes: <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY21-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY21-10-K\">FY21-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY22-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY22-10-K\">FY22-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY23-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY23-10-K\">FY23-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY24-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY24-10-K\">FY24-10-K</a>, <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-10-K\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-10-K\">FY25-10-K</a>.</p>\n<h3>Total Revenue ($M, calendar year)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Ano</th><th>Total Revenue</th><th>YoY</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>FY20</td><td>182.527</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>FY21</td><td>257.637</td><td><strong>+41%</strong> (boom pandemia + ads recovery)</td></tr><tr><td>FY22</td><td>282.836</td><td><strong>+10%</strong> (deceleração ads)</td></tr><tr><td>FY23</td><td>307.394</td><td><strong>+9%</strong> (cost discipline ano)</td></tr><tr><td>FY24</td><td>350.018</td><td><strong>+14%</strong> (re-acceleração)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY25</strong></td><td><strong>402.836</strong></td><td><strong>+15%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Revenue por Segmento ($M)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>FY23</th><th>FY24</th><th><strong>FY25</strong></th><th>YoY 24→25</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Google Search &amp; other</td><td>175.033</td><td>198.084</td><td><strong>224.532</strong></td><td>+13%</td></tr><tr><td>YouTube ads</td><td>31.510</td><td>36.147</td><td><strong>40.367</strong></td><td>+12%</td></tr><tr><td>Google Network</td><td>31.312</td><td>30.359</td><td><strong>29.792</strong></td><td>-2% (declínio estrutural)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Google advertising total</strong></td><td>237.855</td><td>264.590</td><td><strong>294.691</strong></td><td>+11%</td></tr><tr><td>Google subs/platforms/devices</td><td>34.688</td><td>40.340</td><td><strong>48.030</strong></td><td>+19%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Google Services total</strong></td><td>272.543</td><td>304.930</td><td><strong>342.721</strong></td><td>+12%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Google Cloud</strong></td><td>33.088</td><td>43.229</td><td><strong>58.705</strong></td><td><strong>+36%</strong> ← acelerou</td></tr><tr><td>Other Bets</td><td>1.527</td><td>1.648</td><td>1.537</td><td>-7%</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>Operating Income por Segmento ($M)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>FY23</th><th>FY24</th><th><strong>FY25</strong></th><th>YoY 24→25</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Google Services</td><td>95.858</td><td>121.263</td><td><strong>139.404</strong></td><td>+15%</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Google Cloud</strong></td><td><strong>1.716</strong></td><td><strong>6.112</strong></td><td><strong>13.910</strong></td><td><strong>+128%</strong> ← gigante</td></tr><tr><td>Other Bets</td><td>(4.095)</td><td>(4.444)</td><td><strong>(7.515)</strong></td><td>maior loss</td></tr><tr><td>Alphabet-level activities</td><td>(9.186)</td><td>(10.541)</td><td><strong>(16.760)</strong></td><td>shared AI R&amp;D ↑</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Total OP</strong></td><td><strong>84.293</strong></td><td><strong>112.390</strong></td><td><strong>129.039</strong></td><td><strong>+15%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<h3>GCP — operating margin trajectory</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Ano</th><th>GCP Revenue</th><th>GCP OP</th><th>OP margin</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>FY23</td><td>33,088</td><td>1,716</td><td><strong>5,2%</strong></td></tr><tr><td>FY24</td><td>43,229</td><td>6,112</td><td><strong>14,1%</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>FY25</strong></td><td><strong>58,705</strong></td><td><strong>13,910</strong></td><td><strong>23,7%</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>+18,5pp de margin expansion em 2 anos</strong>. Diferentemente do AWS/Azure (margins 30-40% bem estabelecidos), GCP estava queimando capital até FY22-23. <strong>Inflexão clara</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Análise da trajetória</h3>\n<ol><li><strong>FY20 → FY21 (boom pandêmico)</strong>: revenue +41% — combinação pandemia (digital ads) + comp baixo. Pico do ciclo.</li><li><strong>FY22 (ads recession + tech layoffs)</strong>: deceleração para +10%. Fim do &quot;free money era&quot;. Início da &quot;Year of Efficiency&quot; similar a Meta/Amazon.</li><li><strong>FY23 (&quot;cost discipline year&quot;)</strong>: revenue +9% mas OP margin EXPANDIU. GCP virou OP positivo (1,7bn) pela primeira vez.</li><li><strong>FY24 (re-acceleração + AI gear-up)</strong>: revenue +14%. <strong>GCP OP triplicou</strong> ($1,7bn → $6,1bn). EBIT margin Alphabet bateu 32%.</li><li><strong>FY25 (AI infra delivery year)</strong>: revenue +15%. <strong>GCP OP $13,9bn (+128%) com margin 23,7%</strong> — segmento mais impressionante em qualquer hyperscaler. Gemini 2 + Ironwood TPU + Anthropic deal de scale.</li><li><strong>Q4 FY25 specific (per FT 26-Apr-2026)</strong>: GCP <strong>+48% YoY</strong> — aceleração contínua. FY26 on-track para <strong>&gt;$70bn</strong> (vs $58,7bn FY25 → +19%, mas momentum sugere mais).</li></ol>\n<h3>Mix evolution (% of net sales)</h3>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><thead><tr><th>Segmento</th><th>FY23</th><th>FY25</th><th>ΔShare</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Google Cloud</td><td>10,8%</td><td><strong>14,6%</strong></td><td><strong>+3,8pp</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Google subs/platforms</td><td>11,3%</td><td>11,9%</td><td>+0,6pp</td></tr><tr><td>Google advertising</td><td>77,4%</td><td>73,2%</td><td>-4,2pp</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p><strong>Cloud capturando ~4pp de share em 2 anos</strong>. Permanece advertising-heavy (~73%), mas a margem expansion vem do mix shift para Cloud + subscriptions.</p></section>\n<section class=\"wiki-sec\"><h2>FY25 trimestral — narrativa de execução</h2><p>Adicionado <strong>2026-04-27</strong> via ingestão de 4 earnings calls FY25 (FactSet Final Transcripts).</p>\n<h3>Q1 FY25 (Apr-2025) <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q1-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-Q1-earnings-call\">FY25-Q1-earnings-call</a></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Google Services revenue: $77bn (+10% YoY)</strong> — Search + YouTube driving</li><li><strong>Cloud growing rapidly</strong> — Cloud Next conferência destacando AI leadership em infrastructure, agents, more</li><li><strong>270M+ paid subscriptions</strong> (YouTube + Google One drivers)</li><li>AI Mode em Search rolling out</li><li><strong>Lens shopping +10% YoY</strong> — majority of queries are incremental</li><li>Demand Gen + PMax: clientes vendo +2,7x conversion (Royal Canin case study)</li></ul>\n<h3>Q2 FY25 (Jul-2025) <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q2-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-Q2-earnings-call\">FY25-Q2-earnings-call</a></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Google Services revenue: $83bn (+12% YoY)</strong></li><li><strong>Cloud annual run rate &gt;$50bn</strong> — primeira vez acima desse milestone</li><li><strong>Gemini usage +35x YoY</strong> — adoption explosion (LVMH, Salesforce, DBS Bank casos)</li><li>Search: overall queries + commercial queries growing YoY; <strong>AI features drive MORE search</strong></li><li>YouTube: streaming watch time líder US 2+ anos seguidos; 40bn hours sports content global</li></ul>\n<h3>Q3 FY25 (Oct-2025) <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q3-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-Q3-earnings-call\">FY25-Q3-earnings-call</a></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>Google Services revenue: $87bn</strong>, <strong>Search &amp; other +15%</strong></li><li><strong>Cloud accelerating</strong> — backlog +46% QoQ para $155bn</li><li><strong>300M+ paid subscriptions</strong> (era 270M no Q1)</li><li><strong>GCP customers: +34% novos clientes YoY</strong></li><li><strong>Cloud deals &gt;$1bn em 2025: mais que os dois anos anteriores combinados</strong></li><li><strong>70%+ dos GCP customers existentes usam AI products</strong></li><li>Cloud GenAI revenue: <strong>+200% YoY</strong></li><li>150 customers cada processando ~1tn tokens em 12 meses</li></ul>\n<h3>Q4 FY25 (Feb-2026) — <strong>inflection clara</strong> <a class=\"wikilink\" href=\"obsidian://open?vault=equity-research-vault&amp;file=FY25-Q4-earnings-call\" title=\"raw-md/GOOGL/FY25-Q4-earnings-call\">FY25-Q4-earnings-call</a></h3>\n<p><strong>Headline numbers:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>Alphabet annual revenue &gt;$400bn</strong> pela primeira vez (final $403bn)</li><li><strong>Q4 consolidated revenue $113.8bn (+18%)</strong> — aceleração vs Q3</li><li><strong>Gemini 3 launched</strong> — major milestone</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Por segmento (Q4):</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>Google Services: $95.9bn (+14%)</strong></li><li><strong>Search &amp; Other: $63.1bn (+17%)</strong> — broad strength em todos verticais, Retail particularly strong</li><li><strong>YouTube ad: $11.4bn (+9%)</strong> — direct response driving</li><li><strong>Network ad: $7.8bn (-2%)</strong> — declínio estrutural continua</li><li><strong>Subscription/platforms/devices: $13.6bn (+17%)</strong> — YouTube Music + Premium + Google One AI plans</li><li><strong>Cloud Q4: aceleração para +48% YoY</strong> (vs Q1 ~+30%) — annual run rate &gt;$70bn</li><li><strong>Cloud Operating Income Q4: $5.3bn (+&gt;100% YoY)</strong> — margin <strong>30,1%</strong></li></ul>\n<p><strong>Cloud backlog explosão:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>$240bn end of Q4 2025</strong></li><li><strong>+55% QoQ</strong>, <strong>&gt;2x YoY</strong></li><li>Driven por enterprise AI offerings + multiple customers</li><li><strong>Apple deal</strong>: Apple&#x27;s preferred cloud provider, develop next-gen Apple Foundation Models on Gemini</li></ul>\n<p><strong>Gemini adoption:</strong></p>\n<ul><li><strong>120,000+ enterprises</strong> usando Gemini</li><li><strong>95% of top 20 SaaS</strong> companies usam Gemini</li><li><strong>80% of top 100 SaaS</strong> usam Gemini (Salesforce, Shopify, etc.)</li><li><strong>Q4 GenAI products revenue: +400% YoY</strong> (acelerando vs Q3 +200%)</li><li>December: ~350 customers processaram &gt;100bn tokens cada</li></ul>\n<p><strong>FY25 P&amp;L:</strong></p>\n<ul><li>Revenue $403bn (+15%)</li><li>CapEx FY25 actual: <strong>$91.4bn</strong> (Q4 alone $27.9bn)</li><li>Allocation: 60% servers, 40% data centers + networking</li><li>D&amp;A FY25: <strong>$21.1bn (+38%)</strong> vs $15.3bn FY24 — accelerating impact of CapEx</li><li>Long-term debt: $46.5bn</li></ul>\n<h3><strong>FY26 Guidance (Q4 FY25 call):</strong></h3>\n<ul><li><strong>CapEx FY26: $175-185bn</strong> — <strong>~2x FY25</strong> ($91.4bn)<ul><li>Driver: AI compute capacity para frontier model dev (DeepMind), user experience improvements, advertiser ROI em Services, Cloud customer demand</li><li>Allocation: ~60% servers, ~40% long-duration assets (similar a FY25)</li><li><strong>Just over half of ML compute</strong> vai para customer-facing workloads</li></ul></li><li><strong>D&amp;A growth rate em 2026 vai acelerar em Q1 e meaningfully increase full year</strong></li><li>Hiring contínuo em AI + Cloud</li><li>Sundar/Anat: &quot;supply-constrained, even ramping capacity&quot; — <strong>demand &gt; supply</strong></li></ul></section>", "insider": "<div class=\"empty-view\"><p>Sem dados de <strong>Insider Trading</strong> na wiki ainda.</p><p class=\"hint\">Esta view será populada quando a seção correspondente existir em <code>wiki/GOOGL.md</code>.</p></div>"}, "source": "wiki/GOOGL.md", "built_at": "2026-06-09"};
